comments: McDaniels (PHI) contests the driving shot attempt and brushes Murray's (ATL) left arm after the gather.
Reed (PHI) establishes himself in Hunter's (ATL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Hunter (ATL) moves forward and initiates body contact with Milton (PHI) that affects his post shot attempt.
Capela (ATL) establishes himself in McDaniels' (PHI) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
McDaniels (PHI) contests Murray's (ATL) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
Collins (ATL) brushes Milton's (PHI) arm during the shot attempt near the rim.
Collins (ATL) establishes himself in Springer's (PHI) path and marginal foot to foot contact occurs as the pick is set.
House Jr. (PHI) initiates contact with Capela's (ATL) arm, which affects his play at the basket.
Young (ATL) moves alongside Springer's (PHI) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Springer (PHI) brings his arms slightly forward and marginal contact occurs with Young's (ATL) body during his driving shot attempt.
Collins (ATL) cleanly blocks the shot attempt before it reaches its apex and before making contact with the backboard.
Springer (PHI) brings his arm toward Young's (ATL) path and marginal contact occurs at the start of the drive.
The shot clock expires before Young (ATL) releases his shot attempt.
Murray (ATL) legally contests Milton's (PHI) last-second shot attempt.
McDaniels (PHI) contests the driving shot attempt and marginal body contact occurs with Murray (ATL) after the release.
Springer (PHI) brings his arms toward Murray (ATL) and marginal contact occurs as the pick is set.
Reed (PHI) deflects the ball out of bounds.
Capela (ATL) establishes himself in Springer's (PHI) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Springer (PHI) initiates contact with Young's (ATL) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Collins (ATL) is drawn into the air on the shot fake and more than marginal body contact occurs with Springer (PHI) that affects his shot attempt near the rim.
Springer (PHI) briefly places a hand on Young's (ATL) body and the contact is marginal and does not affect his SQBR.
Capela (ATL) establishes a screening position and marginal contact occurs with Milton (PHI) as the screen is set.
